# About Me — [ Your Name ]

> Master profile and single source of truth, UNIQUE TO YOU. Every person who uses this workspace has
> a different identity, history, family, finances, and personality — so this file is yours alone and
> is never shared. `/onboard` (the deep Taste Interview) fills it with YOUR life, not anyone else's.
> Every writing skill and qa-gate reads this alongside `voice-profile.md`, `.claude/rules/voice.md`,
> and `anti-ai.md`. Replace every `[ xxx ]`. Go deep — vague answers make generic content.
>
> **REFER, DO NOT ASSUME.** Skills use only what is actually recorded here. If a fact, story, number,
> name, or detail isn't in this file, they ask for it or leave it out — they never invent, infer, or
> "fill in" your lived experience. Missing material gets flagged (e.g. `[needs: …]`), never guessed.

